{"_id":"YlSZepEr8hex0vWv","name":"Voice of the Spirits","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-scenario-gift-Voice of the Spirits-0"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Requirement</h3><p>You have come into contact with the Gift Spirit.</p><h3>Effect</h3><p>By calming your mind and concentrating, you can open your mind to the spiritual world and communicate with restless souls. Spend 1 Soma to contact a creature with the Spirit Gift you’ve previously encountered. You do not suffer the Wound caused by the stress of spiritual connection.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift. Legacy Iskra adventure support from local backups.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242149,"modifiedTime":1783973242149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"nsLwnAjKz27oRwbS","name":"Wolf-killer","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-scenario-gift-Wolf-killer-1"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Requirement</h3><p>Having faced the wolves in a fight at least once.</p><h3>Effect</h3><p>You know how to deal with the fiercest of wolves and are careful not to be surrounded. When you obtain at least a Standard Outcome on a Position or Defense Check against a pack of beasts, you can immediately eliminate 1 Minor animal NPC with 1 Wound.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift. Legacy Iskra adventure support from local backups.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242149,"modifiedTime":1783973242149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5uH81I1GFIjYhSvC","name":"Where are you going all alone, sweetie?","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-scenario-gift-Where are you going all alone, sweetie?-2"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Requirement</h3><p>To meet Iskra alone in the forest.</p><h3>Effect</h3><p>You are attracted to the little girl who pretends to be a wolf and you dream of devouring her. Once per Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to know exactly where she is. If you anticipate her and arrive somewhere before her, you get 1 Additional Success on every Check you make to hurt or devour that little morsel. You can’t wait to swallow that tidbit and it makes you let your guard down. As long as she is present in the Scene, you receive 1 Penalty in all Defense Checks.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift. Legacy Iskra adventure support from local backups.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242149,"modifiedTime":1783973242149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dgboL8H0LEHkDGLy","name":"Blood Drawings in the Den","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-torn-brown-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Blood Drawings in the Den-0"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Crude drawings on the cave walls of the wolves' den, depicting a mother and daughter holding hands. They are drawn in blood, a haunting testament to Iskra's lost innocence and her desperate longing for the maternal love she was denied. These drawings reveal the tragic humanity still present within the wolf-girl.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Blood Drawings in the Den.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242149,"modifiedTime":1783973242149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bSl4tyl4BOFiHYxU","name":"Elizaveta's Poison","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Elizaveta's Poison-1"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A powerful poison that Elizaveta keeps hidden in the palace. If Iskra is captured, Elizaveta will attempt to use this poison to eliminate her unwanted daughter once and for all. The poison is potent enough to kill even someone with supernatural resilience.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Elizavetas Poison.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SlUDkRybsTid8vuj","name":"Gerard's Letter to the Papacy","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-worn-tan-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Gerard's Letter to the Papacy-2"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A letter written in Lord Gerard Dubois' trembling hand, sent to the Papacy begging for help. The letter reads: 'The beasts that menace the Gévaudan are unnatural, fashioned by something other than God.' This desperate plea brought the Order's Hunters to Durfort.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Gerards Letter to the Papacy.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8nq1cZqBkf27sNQP","name":"Iskra's Pendant","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/jewelry/necklace-pendant-moon-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Iskra's Pendant-3"}},"system":{"description":"<p>An old earthenware pendant that Iskra once made for her mother as a gift, a memento of a rare moment of happiness. Elizaveta tried to dispose of it by throwing it into the old well at the cemetery, but it can still be found at the bottom of the well. This handmade pendant is crude but touching, showing the innocent love of a child for her mother.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Iskras Pendant.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XWTcN87Yf8hSBix2","name":"Iskra's Red Cape","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/equipment/back/cloak-layered-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Iskra's Red Cape-4"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A threadbare red cape, the last gift from Iskra's mother before she sent her daughter to her supposed death in the forest. Despite its worn condition, Iskra still wears it as both a memory and a symbol of her quest for revenge. The cape is stained with mud and blood from her time living as a wolf.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Iskras Red Cape.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MVIBG1whitQLiPcj","name":"Iskra's Wolf Mask","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-wood-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Iskra's Wolf Mask-5"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A rudimentary wooden mask carved by Iskra's own hands to hide her face. The mask depicts a wolf's features and serves both to conceal her identity and to express her adopted nature as part of Greskar's wolf pack. The craftsmanship is crude but effective, showing her adaptation to survival in the wild.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Iskras Wolf Mask.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hCfQ34jKjClyL0zo","name":"Portrait of Patrick Dubois","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/misc/portrait-painting-frame.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Portrait of Patrick Dubois-6"}},"system":{"description":"<p>An enormous painting of Patrick Dubois, Gerard's late father, hanging in the ceremonial hall. The portrait shows a stern and sullen-looking man who seems to judge his son's incompetence from beyond the grave with ill-concealed contempt. Every room in the palace is filled with flattering paintings of Patrick, a constant reminder of Gerard's inadequacy.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Portrait of Patrick Dubois.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242150,"modifiedTime":1783973242150,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"p4b4rMBWtEtyPCbc","name":"Wolf Tracks and Child's Footprints","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/misc/paw-print.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"iskra-story-element-Wolf Tracks and Child's Footprints-7"}},"system":{"description":"<p>In the old cemetery, there are many wolf tracks scattered throughout the grounds. Hidden among them are the prints of two small bare feet, almost certainly belonging to a little girl. These tracks lead deep into the Gévaudan forest, toward the wolves' den. This evidence suggests that a child is somehow involved with the wolf pack.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra adventure element. Legacy file: Wolf Tracks and Childs Footprints.json.","category":"Scenario Support"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973242151,"modifiedTime":1783973242151,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
